				<div class="postright">
					<h3>firefox &amp; thunderbird don&#039;t work at &quot;GDK_USE_XFT=0&amp;</h3>
					<div class="postmsg">
						<p>Hi !<br />I prefer to use x-font(bitmap font) at firefox or thunderbird rather than ttf-font.<br />I&#039;ve used x-font by setting &quot;GDK_USE_XFT=0&quot; at firefox or thunderbird.<br />After I updated pango package several days ago, firefox &amp; thunderbird&#160; have not worked as below.<br />$&#160; GDK_USE_XFT=0 firefox<br />/opt/mozilla/lib/firefox-1.0.7/firefox-bin: symbol lookup error: /opt/mozilla/lib/firefox-1.0.7/components/libgfx_gtk.so: undefined symbol: pango_x_font_map_for_display$&#160; GDK_USE_XFT=0 thunderbird<br />/opt/mozilla/lib/thunderbird-1.0.7/thunderbird-bin: symbol lookup error: /opt/mozilla/lib/thunderbird-1.0.7/components/libgfx_gtk.so: undefined symbol: pango_x_font_map_for_display<br />If I use ttf-font by setting &quot;GDK_USE_XFT=1&quot;, firefox &amp; thunderbird work well.<br />Is there any solution to use x-font at firefox &amp; thunderbird ?</p><p>Sorry about my poor english !</p>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
